    <h2>Systems Thinking for Designers</h2>
  </div>

  <div class="col-2">
    <p>Systems and complexity are all around us - in the products and services we build, in the organizations we are a part of, and in the society we live in. We are systems embedded in systems embedded in systems. This workshop will help designers understand the fundamentals of systems thinking, how to apply systems thinking to organizational complexity, and how to take a systems perspective when designing products and services. </p>

    <h5>LEARNING OUTCOMES</h5>
      <ul class="bullets">
        <li>An understanding of the various types of systems we enounter and work with on a daily basis</li>
        <li>Familiarity with the tools and methodologies used in systems thinking</li>
        <li>Hands-on experience working with complexity and leverage points</li>
        <li>Familiarity with the differences between conventional thinking and systems thinking</li>
      </ul>
  </div>
</section>

